"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Cris John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwBeAjqwNmiMC9tpJ0e1qcNn3H1t8deeQB8L5l2skWnoq6iQk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience here from start to finish. I first scheduled online after reading the reviews, and almost immediately received a call from the office to confirm my appointment and walk me through what they needed. I was able to fill out all the intake forms online, and when there was a hiccup with my insurance they followed up, double-checked everything, and got it sorted quickly. Their communication was very clear, and the automated text reminders for upcoming appointments are a huge help because my schedule is so busy.\n\nWhen I arrived, the front desk team was warm and welcoming. We even joked about the music playing, which happened to be from my high school era, and the waiting area was clean and comfortable. The tech assistant who did my x-rays  was very friendly and easy to talk to. We ended up chatting about her daughter and Pokémon cards, which helped me relax a lot.\n\nThe dentist was thorough, kind, and very clear in explaining what she saw on my x-rays and what my treatment options were. I especially appreciated the detailed written treatment  plan and cost estimate, broken down by phase with what insurance is expected to cover and what my portion would be. Everything felt professional, transparent, and efficient. I left with a clear plan, my next appointment booked, and the sense that my oral health is back on the right track. I’d definitely recommend this office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tim R (Neon Demon)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkHr2-28-1nQv8TVKGGV-lBHwS70M2o-RPasp9qbH4l1PcSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time patient and the service was awesome!  The receptionist was very nice and welcoming. My X-rays were painless and My dentist Dr Prem and hygienist Chris were exceptional! Everyone checked in if I had any questions or needed deeper explanation. When I asked my dentist a question she happily took the time to make sure the answer was satisfactory! I have anxiety and my hygienist was thorough and kind during my cleaning. Making sure that I was comfortable and if I needed to take any breaks, which due to her style I did just fine.\n\nDefinitely check this place out!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Jacquin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZBCaU-A8b0wkBsbZcwY9_9Cl-xTe4KN-CkxPx-F_QnUUTEg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything went better than my best expectations. I am experiencing no pain or any other adverse symptoms. Dr Amani and Tabitha were great and did their best to keep me calm.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Q7 MAMİ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWA5A3Z1Zv0xiH1UL2WUoA0f1be3lr1-0mZgTA9uKSVXXdIjng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Charged $105 for a refused X-ray + 5-minute \"cleaning\" scam. I wouldn’t write this review if my cleaning would really worth\n\"I sincerely wish I had waited for my regular dentist. I only came here because I couldn't get an appointment in my dentist they didn’t have availability , and it was a huge mistake.\nMy insurance covers my cleaning 100%, yet I walked out paying $105 out of pocket. Why? Because they forced an X-ray on me that I explicitly refused (I had already sent them my 3D X-ray). To make matters worse, my wife visited this exact location a few days ago for the same service and was not charged for an X-ray. The inconsistency is unacceptable.\nThe quality of care was shocking. The assistant rushed through the polishing like she was buffering a car frame—just aggressive and fast. Then the doctor came in, sprayed some pressurized water for a few minutes, and called it done. The whole thing took 5 minutes.\nMy regular dentist spends 30 minutes ensuring every corner is clean. This place gave me a rushed, substandard rinse and a bill for a service I said 'no' to. Do not go here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marie Bailey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZmPMVnNjuOLcKMPjayCYB47E7yRGfcy8HgPu_PkVVb1uDAA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Having a tooth extracted is never fun. I so appreciated the excellent care. Wonderful team and I enjoy their sense humor and the care they provide.\n\nI really admire the whole team. They all made me feel relaxed and cared for. Thanks to all for amazing care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sydney Horen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnQkpFg3Xg-8wGRpBjPxC4IWAAGskHIMD1uEVAFywWkclsb13w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don’t write negative reviews most of the time but had such a terrible experience that I need to deter folks from choosing this place. I had my wisdom teeth extraction done here. Prior to my appointment, I had my insurance gather an estimate of treatments and costs prior to my appointment, since Gentle Dental initially quoted me at $6000.  The new estimate the clinic gave was supposed to be $860 but a dental hygienist quoted me at $2030 when I was there for my appointment. Not to mention, the dental team and the front office could not agree on who was supposed to relay billing info to the patient and had an argument regarding this right in front of me in the waiting room. This resulted in my dental team being short with me because they were cooling down from the argument. The dental hygienist also complained about the front office team directly to me, while prepping me for my surgery. I also was almost not able to receive my surgery because no one told me I couldn’t have water 10 hours beforehand. There was no communication from the clinic prior to my appointment regarding this. Luckily, the dentist decided to follow through with the surgery. Otherwise, it would have been a waste of time. Once the appointment was done, someone from the dental team wheeled me out of the office but gave neither me nor my fiance instructions on how to care for myself post-wisdom teeth extraction. We had to call after we left the clinic and then drive back to get the goody bag and instructions they didn’t give us. Awful experience and I’m switching my dentist after this.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jim caroompas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyIG_wal7Q27K_meZGewwmUZBOZEzu_KYK5MI420J3LbUo_Io=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At age 71, I've had my share of dental experiences. None has ever come close to the care and skill of this team! I had an infected molar extracted, a difficult procedure. But not at all painful (until the novocaine wears off!), and I know the job he did was first-rate. His assistant was equally skilled and attentive, and I felt in the best of hands the entire time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven Caulk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVItq6P1Yu1w4emC2M56akLGPeSiaC93jhapn5LtP7Mluduxp0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never a fan of the dentist.   However the staff and the doctor during my visit were really kind and caring.  They took the time to assuage any fears i had and explained the pre inspection through to the post consultation with explanations of all the issues and discussed what they found with potential solutions.\nThey also created a quote of the breakdown of the costs and answered any medical or financial questions I had.\nThey made the whole experience a good one.  Better than i have had in the past with any other dentists.  Good enough that I'm willing to start going to the dentist again.   Thank you everyone at Mill Creek Gentle Dental!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
