ption":"Staff is warm and welcoming.  Dental hygienists are sensitive and very good at their job. They do such a good job, it keeps me from having dental issues.   Dr. Tony and Dr. Matt are the top in their field.  I highly recommend this team!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa Evans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0IwnQcx-1tW3pKRsLt1hBJ3TN7qG1Nhxp-rgEy5E535Yk1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this office. Dr. Santorsola and Dr. Su are both great. Well educated and very skilled dentists. The hygienists are very well trained - gentle, thorough and kind. The view is just icing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robin Haedt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUq-ccDxvyxPy6_mdoLS8BtteZkBJLNUxFfFVDPGrHoowpHvmY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm no stranger to the dentist that's for sure. I've had a lot of work done. I've seen many dentists throughout my lifetime. I moved to the Seattle area and was looking for a dentist. I asked my periodontist who he goes to because if anybody knows a good dentist it would be a periodontist and because I hadn't found a new dentist yet, he was able to recommend his. I'm so glad I asked. Best dentist I've ever been to. He takes his time. He's patient and very gentle. When Dr. Santorsola heard that just received custody of my grandkids. He made sure to let me know that he supported my husband and I 100% and would do all in any work that they needed done at no cost. There are many many reasons why I continue to see him year after year.\nI recently needed to get in ASAP for a chipped tooth. I was able to get right in  to see Dr. Su and was very pleased with my service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Linda Dolstad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIh4KosenH0NowOS0Rq811c3zK1y_U21j8NJJrQD9MaKyQVQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"By far this is the very best dentist I have ever been to. When you walk in the door you are greeted with a smile. I had implants done by Dr Tony a few years ago \u0026 his work is amazing. Love him! If you are looking for a dentist I can’t recommend Kenmore Dentistry enough.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy Beach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCvxFanA-di0ydpcc11gbX-VyDK88xFEYiNizFlAruNcxCHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife and kids have been going to Kenmore Denistry for over 10 years and have been very happy with them. So when I needed a dentist I figured I would give them a try and I would have to say they were great. I want to say thanks to their friendly staff and Matthew Su DDS for helping me with some challenging dental issues that I have. They have been great and are helping me get back to  better dental health.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peg Stevens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnogaE9jrYMQqoVmCU-XL4rH_jtwNz5AU2T0RFYePrH5db4A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I saw Elizabeth for the first time yesterday and she was very kind and professional. I’ve had great experiences with all hygienists. Dr Santorsola has been a wonderful dentist and in recommending other professionals for my braces to ENT needs over the years.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dani Bates","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIIqHpczHk8C64kutcHjiL-BYqyZP291PLV5DzU13peYsZlgpZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A dentist where you get actual dentistry done, not a place where they just push unnecessary restorative work. The staff I’ve met are all very nice and knowledgeable. Professional yet approachable. And if that’s not enough, the view from the treatment chair is divine, a full view of Lake Washington.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patricia L Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9srpNxkWdC2kAwBZd4Ass1qPl4o4DdoftfVC6KCS4jOdxfErlHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had my teeth cleaned by Jackie yesterday. She did a great job and suggested a protective coating on a tooth with a cavity forming.\nDr. Santarsola is leaving the practice and it was his last day. He is fully retiring. I met the new doctor, Matt Su, who agreed with Jackie's suggestion for the cavity. He seems to be caring and technically very good. I am planning to stay with the practice.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
