ive! I haven't had a cavity in my life and I'm grateful for their advice! Definitely try a cleaning here!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Keith Leggett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLzFs3wm95r-a2_IbLkbN6O4opYG_5ddQPvvNOkGkXn8ugZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The entire staff exceeded my expectations. Din is amazing. She was thorough, she explained every procedure in advance, answered all of my questions, and gave me the most informative and complete cleaning I have ever had... and I've had a lot of them. I will like it here. My wife will as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marcie Mathison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqHaMQxlmba_Ev2SiY1_aWQTJoADtWodRCyGSRf0-Krwhz8Vc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I LOVE this clinic!  Mountlake Family Dentistry is so  welcoming and personable!  Every single person that works there, greets you and makes me want to stay and chat all day.  Not to mention Dr Luna and Dr Gan are very smart and experts in their dentistry field.  I have complete and total confidence in their abilities and their advice.  I feel the same regarding all the hygienists that take care of me there.   A+++","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nyla Gallant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjPoH8xUigsVOxpgTLp5IbrtDSK7G-L2HVUJlFRacbogJ0FA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time going to Mountlake Family Dentistry. Was quite happy with the hygienist and the dentist. They were very friendly and thorough in my cleaning and explaining everything that I needed to know to take the best care of my teeth. Will be continuing there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ken Winkenweder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWU1dKd91DcT3p5XrVeZCjA5zRoUVcoJlofnhRUYT1o7tZ4ftzT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great dental facility. All the staff are very caring and gentle. Front office makes you feel very comfortable. Glad I found this dentistry many years ago!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Misty Goldstone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6wkCeKqeb3FA1Z4sjRDvg5v4lyVWlQHL-5oAWv8xVvQUjlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Going to the dentist is not on my list of fun things to do yet this dental office did their best to ensure my comfort. The team was knowledgeable, professional and actively listened to my concerns. Thank you Doctor!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca Ortega","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbbMtwk8bB-xjBhix5SPbhOJWNukOfjamXtfCam-CYygZa-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Like most folks, I don't await dental appointments with great eagerness, but the staff at Mountlake Family Dentistry are truly lovely. I've seen Dr. Gan most of the visits, she is very cheerful and efficient. I've seen several different hygienists with no complaints, they are gentle, friendly, and don't ask you too many questions while your mouth is stuck open. And despite my inconsistent flossing routines, they never shame me! They encourage healthy habits without the guilt trips and do a great job of dental care. Have had a few fillings here with no issues. Pro tip: They also have blankets if you ask nicely since I am always cold in the dentist chair.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nikki Tracey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzG9HsBCN_A0s15IjIzTVSqKrNSgp-ufBt8CkWgQRqEV9XHL8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hello Community! I feel very compelled to warn you all about MountLake Terrace family Dentistry!\n\nFirst of all I should let you all know that I am a Dental Assistant. I have worked in Dentistry for 15 years. I have been out of the field for 3 years since having my daughter. I went in just for a routine dental cleaning. I went in as a new patient. I live a mile away and thought it would be easy and convenient for me. I have never had a cavity in my life! I have close to perfect teeth and have taken very well care of my teeth my entire life! I went in and during the exam the Dentist diagnosed me with a cavity in nearly every molar! I was absolutely shocked and devastated! My perfect teeth were crumbling? I asked the Dentist multiple questions and asked if it was possible to reverse the cavities. She told me no! That they were too deep and far along to reverse. I knew I needed a second opinion. So I waited 6 months and went back to another dentist that I had seen. They did an exam and to my surprise ZERO cavities! ZERO! They recommended no treatment. When I previously walked out of my last exam at Mountlake Terrace family dentistry with about 5k of recommended work to be done 😡\n\nI can’t tell you how infuriating this is. I am familiar with the field and worked in it for nearly two decades. This woman knew my background and still had the audacity to try and drill into my cavity free teeth! Please do not ever step foot into that office. Please be warned that this Dentist is awful! So awful! I have worked with many doctors and this is the worst i have ever come across! If I could picket outside of their office and warn everyone who walked through that door, I would. For her to try this on an experienced Dental Assistant, I can’t imagine the malpractices she is getting away with. I don’t know how she sleeps at night 😡","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
