e payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Patrick O'Callahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRP6a9ePQJkKDVtCeNA4fDFecyjcIZvUS8YXy-9m0PI84smA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been going to Kirkland Dental Partners for years and have always received skilled, conscientious care. All members of the staff have been great. A special shout out for Nela, who has given me particularly detailed and useful advice on long-term care for my teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eugenia García Rojas Alarcón","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmAmYAtPj6KyqAq9w4AMFLOjGgcXhp4OmjTUMoheKOw864fu06=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m so sad Dr Etheridge retired, he was wonderful. I had been his patient for many many years but definitely things have changed so much since he’s not there. In my last cleaning appointment with they declined to do any cleaning unless I accepted a “deep cleaning”, which I already get twice a year a my Periodontist. Instead of a regular cleaning they offered flossing 😳😂😂! This was ridiculous, I floss every night. I was so disappointed that they didn’t listen to me and didn’t care. I won’t be returning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis juarez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHuLYwF8cU3-8Xp2ePuo_BuLEDHsRUpApqvTToLqm28LWJOw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great experience at Kirkland Dental Partners! The staff is so welcoming and professional. Sandra, the dental hygienist, is amazing—she’s gentle, thorough, and makes cleanings so comfortable. Dr. Kim is also wonderful—knowledgeable, kind, and takes the time to explain everything clearly. I always leave feeling well taken care of. Highly recommend this office to anyone looking for quality dental care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maria Pettigrew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSmezxhZQQiINOP3-Lx4HbOKsEnL2_fCSrz6f7Cvj6Wnk25A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was always extremely satisfied with Dr. Philip as my dentist, but my experience with Dr. Eun Kim, who took over his practice, has been very disappointing.\nAt my first appointment, she recommended replacing several crowns and a bridge. She replaced one crown, but the shade came out noticeably darker than the rest of my teeth. When I raised the concern, she did not address it directly and instead had her hygienist call me back. I was told there was nothing more she could do.\nShe is not personable and, in my experience, she is not on your side as a patient.\nBecause of this, I have decided not to return. If you are considering seeing the new dentist, please know that my personal experience was that she rushed and did not provide the same level of care or communication I had with Dr. Philip.\nThe 4.9 rating I’m sure is Dr Phil’s","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Calvin Xu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzU1erIckt91he8ZWXoXZrQzjq5Ds_S9Bsk_vQ68DyC4INp68u=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve already had an unnecessary wisdom tooth removal and a deep cleaning done here, but now they refuse to do a regular cleaning unless I agree to their “suggestion” for a $3,000+ non-reimbursable surgery. I told them I’d consider it next year, but they still refused to see me. Honestly, just too many “suggestions” from this dental office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"a krevus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSpyddCH64E4I_5pPhh7cfG7SfTcPH76xSDpwblOE9ikt_d8xh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I moved to Seattle 4 years ago.\n\nWe all needed a good dentist badly.\n\nI started digging into google “dentist near me.\nIt was so hard. And then I noticed something from Dr. Etheredge’s about us:\nOne of his staff retired.\nSo?\nThe between the lines were, she worked there since the practice open.\nHmmm….\nIf the staffs is in good faith and never treated wrongly, the doctor must have done something right.\n\nAnd I looked at their Facebook, yelp, google reviews,\nAllllll  good!\n\nSo we gave it a try. My three grown up boys all love this place. One of my boy who’s in San Diego for school decided not to look further in San Diego, the front desk is so helpful keeping him on track. That’s what I called “GREAT SERVICE). And, to my surprise, a lot of their patients grew up, moved elsewhere for school, are all coming during summer and winter for their dental care!\nHUH!!\n\nFor my 1 visit, Dr. Etheredge gave me a sixteen points check up, from teeth to jaw bone to chin, to neck.\nWow!!\n\nHe had to help me to remove a 29 year old crown way into the back of my mouth. He was extremely careful, kept asking if I was feeling alright.\nHe said it was a very special metal compound that was very very sturdily mounted (I knew that), but, 29 years can do a lot to the gaps between my tooth and the crown.\nHe removed, cleaned it up thoroughly, removed any cavity decay, tried to leave me some natural tooth so the new crown could grab on to for another 10+ years. He knew that I was timid toward implant, boy had he tried! The result was that my jaw didn’t feel strangled afterwards. Yeap!\n\nHe was getting near his retirement, we went through his search of a new “great dentist” to take care of his loyal patients. I saw how he observed and guided 2 doctors, with the only concern in his mind, for the welfare of his lifelong family, his patients since day one through out!\n\nI Wa deeply moved!\n\nHis hygienist Sandra was also wonderful, gentle (that I treasure), detail oriented, thorough, and so sweet!\n\nThe front desk treats everyone as if we were their long term acquaintances, yet does the job right, courteous and efficiently.\n\n2 thumbs up!\n5 stars!\n\nDr. Kim is the new Doctor, who’s had 20 years of experience, and is willingly joining this office, my boys had filling, routine cleaning up, post ortho cavity check, you name it!\nWe are still in love with this office.\n\nI’m pretty sure you will too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Meryl Brownstein","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEdyuTyzJ6hOpmDsX6xW0qXVogJpkK_-sSIKOTAyO0peCrD1E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Since Dr Phil has retired, the group has found a very nice dentist to take his place. The dental hygienist, Maria, is excellent. I am very pleased with all the new staff.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike Convertino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkrq0im4n3UtJWgyRH51jTxxRslJVYKg158ZJQYFRmg1L_ywdgFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I love having Dr Etheredge as my dentist! My teeth were in bad shape prior to my seeing him due to family predisposition to cavities, but he has repaired everything over the time I’ve been seeing him. Unfortunately, he sold his practice about a year ago and I understand he has now stopped working there. What a loss.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
